description:
Welcome to Harlem! Large bright home-away-from-home on 5th ave. Family friendly 2bed/1bath apt set back from the hustle & bustle, centrally located, easy access to subways & attractions. 4 min walk to subway station, 20 min walk to the met and many more museums knowns in NYC as the Museum Mile! Central Park right across the street!

Th apartment is on the boarder of harlem and upper east side conveniently located on 5th ave next to great subway transportations.

All hardwood floor, fully renovated apt with modern fully equipped kitchen. Master bedroom has queen size bed, 2nd bedroom has full rise bed. Get all your work done on a beautiful desk with very High speed internet. All TV's are smart TVs. 

The living room is large with sofa that can turn into a bed for 1 or 2 small kids. Sofa is 8 feet long and 3 1/2 feet wide beautiful custom leather sofa from restoration hardware. 

Get ready to have beautiful dinners at the dining table capable for 8 people. All hardwood floor, fully renovated apt with modern fully equipped kitchen and all-marble bathroom. Both the rooms have queen size bed, work desk and large wardrobe. High speed internet, smart TV, central heating and AC in the both the rooms. The living room is large with sofa that can turn into a bed and with dining table and 6 chairs.

More about the Rooms & Apartment:

WiFi Included
30 seconds to Central Park
10 min walk to your first Museum
AC included in Each Room (spring,summer and Fall)
3 Blocks from Subway Stations 
NYSC, FreshFoods Supermarket, Restaurants Nearby
Fully Equipped Kitchen
Large Living Room: spacious

I am available throughout the day for any questions or requirements.

The neighborhood is bordered with South Harlem and upper east side, the apt is located in front of central Park with Views of the park from living room.

Central Park is 30 seconds away.

Museums within 5-10 minute walk

110th Street – Museum for African Art 
105th Street – El Museo del Barrio 
103rd Street – Museum of the City of New York 

Museums within 10-20min walk

92nd Street – The Jewish Museum 
91st Street – Cooper-Hewitt, National Design Museum (part of the Smithsonian Institution) 
89th Street – National Academy Museum and School of Fine Arts
88th Street – Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum

Museums within 20 min walk

86th Street – Neue Galerie New York
82nd Street – The Metropolitan Museum of Art

2 and 3 subway line is one block away.

6 subway line is 3 blocks away.

No smoking
Not suitable for pets
No parties or events
May not be safe or suitable for infants (Under 2 years)
